Absolute Radio is famous for being the home of Dave Berry, Jason Manford, Frank Skinner and the No Repeat Guarantee. We champion the very best in rock music, from breaking new acts such as Rag‘n’Bone Man and Blossoms to favourites such as Coldplay and Foo Fighters, along with the best of legends like The Beatles, Bon Jovi and Queen. We don’t do plastic pop pap – we do real guitars, real drums and real singers. Absolute Radio - where real music matters.

Absolute 80s is the UK's only radio station dedicated to playing the undisputed classics of the 1980s. Immerse yourself in a decade of music so infectious that before you know it you'll be reaching for the shoulder pads, pulling on those stonewashed jeans and painting your face like Adam Ant. This is the land of Human League, U2, Frankie Goes to Hollywood, Simple Minds, Duran Duran, Prince, ABC, Depeche Mode, Blondie and Bon Jovi, not forgetting a sprinkle of timeless tunes from artists such as Madonna, Michael Jackson and Culture Club.
PlanetRock plays classic rock hits and album tracks, mainly from the 60s,70s and early 80s.
The world's largest sport radio station

Smooth Radio loves life and loves music, just the way you do. At Smooth Radio we remember the time when music made you want to turn the radio up, not off. We span the greatest soulful sounds from today and the past five decades. From the O'Jays, Stevie Wonder and Barry White to James Morrison, Duffy and Paloma Faith, we don't have to talk about nostalgia, the music we play unlocks the best times of our lives, past and present. On Smooth Radio, there's no mindless chatter, no irate callers, just great music and DJs, such as Simon Bates, Mark Goodier and Pat Sharp, who are both passionate and knowledgeable about the music they play. Entertaining guests occasionally pop in too. Smooth wouldn't interrupt the music for anything less!

LBC 97.3 is London's biggest conversation. Broadcasting to the greatest city in the world, it offers a 24/7 platform for listeners to express their views on the topical issues of the day. Our presenters include some of the best communicators in UK radio including the multi award-winning Nick Ferrari, James O'Brien, Andrew Castle and Larry Lamb. The station is home to Call Clegg, the Deputy Prime Minister's weekly radio show and Ask Boris with the Mayor of London. LBC 97.3 is the only radio station where you can join in intellectual debate and hear expert opinion without distraction around the clock. LBC.co.uk
